Note:
Runa Standard Library: Advanced Inspect Module

Next-generation introspection and reflection system with comprehensive code analysis,
source code inspection, stack frame analysis, and advanced debugging capabilities.
Provides enhanced object inspection that surpasses traditional tools.

Features:
- Comprehensive object inspection and analysis
- Advanced function and method introspection
- Enhanced type system reflection with metadata
- Sophisticated source code analysis with AST processing  
- Advanced call stack inspection and debugging
- Intelligent module and package inspection
- Performance profiling and memory analysis
- Code quality assessment and metrics
- Enhanced debugging with breakpoints and watchpoints
- Real-time execution monitoring and analysis
:End Note

Import "inspect/core" as inspection_core
Import "inspect/source" as source_analysis  
Import "inspect/stack" as stack_inspection
Import "collections/dict" as dict_utils
Import "collections/list" as list_utils
Import "string/format" as string_utils
Import "datetime/datetime" as datetime_module

Note: Enhanced Types for Advanced Inspection
Type ObjectInfo is Dictionary with:
    type_name as String
    module_name as String
    attributes as Dictionary[String, AttributeInfo]
    methods as Dictionary[String, MethodInfo]
    base_types as List[String]
    is_primitive as Boolean
    is_collection as Boolean
    is_callable as Boolean
    size_estimate as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type AttributeInfo is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    type_name as String
    value as Any
    is_readonly as Boolean
    is_property as Boolean
    is_method as Boolean
    access_level as AccessLevel
    documentation as Optional[String]

Type MethodInfo is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    signature as String
    parameters as List[ParameterInfo]
    return_type as Optional[String]
    is_static as Boolean
    is_class_method as Boolean
    is_property as Boolean
    access_level as AccessLevel
    documentation as Optional[String]
    source_location as Optional[SourceLocation]

Type ParameterInfo is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    type_annotation as Optional[String]
    default_value as Optional[Any]
    kind as ParameterKind
    is_required as Boolean

Type ParameterKind is:
    | POSITIONAL_ONLY
    | POSITIONAL_OR_KEYWORD
    | VAR_POSITIONAL
    | KEYWORD_ONLY
    | VAR_KEYWORD

Type AccessLevel is:
    | PUBLIC
    | PROTECTED
    | PRIVATE

Type SourceLocation is Dictionary with:
    filename as String
    line_number as Integer
    column_number as Integer

Type ModuleInfo is Dictionary with:
    name as String
    filename as String
    package as Optional[String]
    functions as List[String]
    classes as List[String]
    variables as List[String]
    submodules as List[String]
    documentation as Optional[String]
    import_dependencies as List[String]

Note: Core Inspection Functions

Process inspect with target as Any:
    Note: Comprehensive object inspection using core library
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    Return result

Process get_members with target as Any:
    Note: Get all members of an object
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    Return inspection_result.members

Process get_signature with function as Any:
    Note: Get function signature information  
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let function_info be inspection_core.inspect_function with inspector as inspector and function as function
    Return inspection_core.get_function_signature with function as function

Process get_source_code with target as Any:
    Note: Get source code for an object
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    If inspection_result.source_info.available:
        Return inspection_result.source_info.source_code
    Otherwise:
        Return ""

Process get_documentation with target as Any:
    Note: Get documentation string for an object
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    Return inspection_result.documentation

Process get_module_info with module as Any:
    Note: Get comprehensive module information
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let module_info be inspection_core.inspect_module with inspector as inspector and module as module
    Return module_info

Process get_class_info with class as Any:
    Note: Get comprehensive class information
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let class_info be inspection_core.inspect_class with inspector as inspector and class as class
    Return class_info

Note: Source Code Analysis Functions

Process analyze_source_file with filename as String:
    Note: Analyze a source code file
    Let analyzer be source_analysis.create_source_analyzer
    Let analysis_result be source_analysis.analyze_source_file with analyzer as analyzer and filename as filename
    Return analysis_result

Process parse_source_code with source_code as String:
    Note: Parse source code into AST
    Let analyzer be source_analysis.create_source_analyzer
    Let parse_result be source_analysis.parse_source_code with analyzer as analyzer and source_code as source_code
    Return parse_result

Process get_source_metrics with source_code as String:
    Note: Calculate source code metrics
    Let analyzer be source_analysis.create_source_analyzer
    Let parse_result be source_analysis.parse_source_code with analyzer as analyzer and source_code as source_code
    If parse_result.success:
        Let metrics be source_analysis.calculate_source_metrics with 
            calculator as analyzer.metric_calculator and 
            source as source_code and 
            ast as parse_result.ast_tree
        Return metrics
    Otherwise:
        Return None

Process validate_syntax with source_code as String:
    Note: Validate source code syntax
    Let analyzer be source_analysis.create_source_analyzer
    Let validation_result be source_analysis.validate_syntax with analyzer as analyzer and source_code as source_code
    Return validation_result

Process format_source with source_code as String:
    Note: Format source code according to style guidelines
    Let analyzer be source_analysis.create_source_analyzer
    Let formatted_code be source_analysis.format_source_code with analyzer as analyzer and source_code as source_code
    Return formatted_code

Note: Stack Inspection and Debugging Functions

Process get_current_stack:
    Note: Get current call stack information
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let stack_result be stack_inspection.inspect_current_stack with inspector as inspector
    Return stack_result

Process get_current_frame:
    Note: Get current execution frame
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Return inspector.current_frame

Process get_frame_info with depth as Integer:
    Note: Get frame information at specific depth
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let frames be stack_inspection.capture_enhanced_stack_frames with inspector as inspector
    If depth is less than frames.length:
        Return frames[depth]
    Otherwise:
        Return None

Process start_tracing:
    Note: Start execution tracing
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let tracer_id be stack_inspection.start_execution_tracing with inspector as inspector
    Return tracer_id

Process stop_tracing with inspector as Any:
    Note: Stop execution tracing and return results
    Let trace_data be stack_inspection.stop_execution_tracing with inspector as inspector
    Return trace_data

Process add_breakpoint with filename as String and line_number as Integer:
    Note: Add a breakpoint at specified location
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let breakpoint_id be stack_inspection.add_breakpoint with 
        inspector as inspector and 
        filename as filename and 
        line_number as line_number
    Return breakpoint_id

Process add_conditional_breakpoint with filename as String and line_number as Integer and condition as String:
    Note: Add a conditional breakpoint
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let breakpoint_id be stack_inspection.add_conditional_breakpoint with 
        inspector as inspector and 
        filename as filename and 
        line_number as line_number and 
        condition as condition
    Return breakpoint_id

Process add_watchpoint with variable_name as String and watch_type as Any:
    Note: Add a variable watchpoint
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let watchpoint_id be stack_inspection.add_watchpoint with 
        inspector as inspector and 
        variable_name as variable_name and 
        watch_type as watch_type
    Return watchpoint_id

Process analyze_recursion:
    Note: Analyze recursion patterns in current stack
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let recursion_analysis be stack_inspection.analyze_recursion_patterns with inspector as inspector
    Return recursion_analysis

Note: Advanced Analysis Functions

Process get_object_info with target as Any:
    Note: Get comprehensive object information
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    
    Let object_info be ObjectInfo with:
        type_name as inspection_result.object_type
        module_name as get_object_module_name with target as target
        attributes as extract_attributes_from_members with members as inspection_result.members
        methods as extract_methods_from_members with members as inspection_result.members
        base_types as get_object_base_types with target as target
        is_primitive as is_primitive_type with target as target
        is_collection as is_collection_type with target as target
        is_callable as is_callable_object with target as target
        size_estimate as estimate_object_size with target as target
        metadata as inspection_result.metadata
    
    Return object_info

Process compare_objects with obj1 as Any and obj2 as Any:
    Note: Compare two objects and identify differences
    Let info1 be get_object_info with target as obj1
    Let info2 be get_object_info with target as obj2
    
    Let comparison be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as comparison and key as "type_match" and value as info1.type_name is equal to info2.type_name
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as comparison and key as "attribute_differences" and value as compare_attributes with attrs1 as info1.attributes and attrs2 as info2.attributes
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as comparison and key as "method_differences" and value as compare_methods with methods1 as info1.methods and methods2 as info2.methods
    
    Return comparison

Process find_references with target as Any and search_scope as Any:
    Note: Find references to an object within a scope
    Let references be list_utils.create_empty_list
    Note: This would require advanced runtime analysis
    Note: Implementation depends on runtime environment capabilities
    Return references

Process get_call_graph:
    Note: Get call graph of current execution
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Let stack_result be stack_inspection.inspect_current_stack with inspector as inspector
    Return stack_result.call_graph

Process profile_performance with function as Any:
    Note: Profile function performance
    Let inspector be stack_inspection.create_stack_inspector
    Note: This would require integration with runtime profiling
    Let performance_data be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
    Return performance_data

Note: Utility Functions

Process is_function with target as Any:
    Note: Check if object is a function
    Let object_info be get_object_info with target as target
    Return object_info.is_callable

Process is_class with target as Any:
    Note: Check if object is a class/type
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    Return inspection_result.object_type is equal to "class"

Process is_module with target as Any:
    Note: Check if object is a module
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    Return inspection_result.object_type is equal to "module"

Process get_type_name with target as Any:
    Note: Get the type name of an object
    Let object_info be get_object_info with target as target
    Return object_info.type_name

Process get_all_attributes with target as Any:
    Note: Get all attributes of an object
    Let object_info be get_object_info with target as target
    Return dict_utils.get_keys with dict as object_info.attributes

Process get_all_methods with target as Any:
    Note: Get all methods of an object
    Let object_info be get_object_info with target as target
    Return dict_utils.get_keys with dict as object_info.methods

Note: Information Display Functions

Process format_object_info with target as Any:
    Note: Format object information for display
    Let inspector be inspection_core.create_inspector
    Let inspection_result be inspection_core.inspect_object with inspector as inspector and target as target
    Let formatted_info be inspection_core.format_object_info with inspection_result as inspection_result
    Return formatted_info

Process format_stack_trace with stack_result as Any:
    Note: Format stack trace for display
    Let formatted_trace be stack_inspection.format_stack_trace with inspection_result as stack_result
    Return formatted_trace

Process display_inspection_summary with target as Any:
    Note: Display comprehensive inspection summary
    Let object_info be get_object_info with target as target
    Let summary_lines be list_utils.create_empty_list
    
    Call list_utils.append with list as summary_lines and item as "Object Inspection Summary:"
    Call list_utils.append with list as summary_lines and item as "  Type: " plus object_info.type_name
    Call list_utils.append with list as summary_lines and item as "  Module: " plus object_info.module_name
    Call list_utils.append with list as summary_lines and item as "  Attributes: " plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as dict_utils.get_size with dict as object_info.attributes
    Call list_utils.append with list as summary_lines and item as "  Methods: " plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as dict_utils.get_size with dict as object_info.methods
    Call list_utils.append with list as summary_lines and item as "  Estimated Size: " plus string_utils.integer_to_string with value as object_info.size_estimate plus " bytes"
    
    Return string_utils.join with list as summary_lines and separator as "\n"

Note: Module Information

Process get_inspect_info:
    Let info be dict_utils.create_empty_dict
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as info and key as "module_name" and value as "inspect"
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as info and key as "version" and value as "3.0.0"
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as info and key as "description" and value as "Advanced introspection and reflection system with comprehensive code analysis, source inspection, and debugging capabilities"
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as info and key as "capabilities" and value as "Object inspection, Source analysis, Stack inspection, Function signatures, Module analysis, Performance profiling, Debugging support"
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as info and key as "core_features" and value as "Enhanced object introspection, AST-based source analysis, Advanced stack inspection, Comprehensive debugging tools"
    Call dict_utils.set_value with dict as info and key as "created_at" and value as string_utils.integer_to_string with value as datetime_module.get_timestamp
    Return info

Note: Helper Functions (Platform Interface Stubs)
Process get_object_module_name with target as Any: Return "unknown_module"
Process extract_attributes_from_members with members as Dictionary[String, Any]: Return dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Process extract_methods_from_members with members as Dictionary[String, Any]: Return dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Process get_object_base_types with target as Any: Return list_utils.create_empty_list
Process is_primitive_type with target as Any: Return false
Process is_collection_type with target as Any: Return false
Process is_callable_object with target as Any: Return false
Process estimate_object_size with target as Any: Return 0
Process compare_attributes with attrs1 as Dictionary[String, AttributeInfo] and attrs2 as Dictionary[String, AttributeInfo]: Return dict_utils.create_empty_dict
Process compare_methods with methods1 as Dictionary[String, MethodInfo] and methods2 as Dictionary[String, MethodInfo]: Return dict_utils.create_empty_dict